"Pipeline model type (default: model.default_type). image_classification builds train/test ImageFolder splits from "
"class subdirectories (all other options above apply); image_generation_lora instead copies every image directly under"
" --raw-data-dir (no class folders, no train/test split) plus its optional .txt caption sidecar into --data-dir, for "
"LoRA fine-tuning of an image-generation model."
msgstr ""

#: mb/cli/parsing/data.py:312
msgid "Rename mislabeled .jpg sources and rebuild CONVERTED JPEGs"
msgstr ""

#: mb/cli/parsing/data.py:314
msgid ""
"Finds non-JPEG bytes under .jpg/.jpeg names in class source trees (same discovery as convert), writes corrected "
"JPEGs, and removes stale copies under CONVERTED and small_images_review only after a successful write. Animated GIFs "
"use the same random-frame + visual_media_review layout as convert when the model type is image_classification."
msgstr ""

#: mb/cli/parsing/data.py:325
msgid ""
"Raw data directory (default: data.raw_data_dir from the pipeline config after --config; same as gather/convert when "
"omitted)."
msgstr ""

#: mb/cli/parsing/data.py:332
msgid "Log planned repairs only; do not rename files or write outputs."
msgstr ""

#: mb/cli/parsing/data.py:339
msgid ""
"Print newline-delimited JSON (stdout): dry-run or live repair. By default only actionable mismatches are listed; use "
"-v to include policy-skipped PNG/WebP/BMP/TIFF under .jpg. Live repair emits one line per successful fix when "
"applicable."
msgstr ""

#: mb/cli/parsing/data.py:348
msgid "With --dry-run and --json: include Pillow format and GIF metadata in each JSON object."
msgstr ""

#: mb/cli/parsing/data.py:355
msgid "With --dry-run: omit verbose per-file log lines (use with --json for machine-readable output only)."
msgstr ""

#: mb/cli/parsing/data.py:364
msgid ""
"With --json: include policy-skipped static-format mismatches in JSON output. In text mode: log each policy-skipped "
"file and class progress for every folder; with live repair, log each skipped file. Useless with --quiet. Separate "
"from top-level mb -v (global logging)."
msgstr ""

#: mb/cli/parsing/data.py:374
msgid ""
"Also rename/repair mislabeled .jpg/.jpeg whose bytes are PNG, WebP, BMP, or TIFF. By default those are counted and "
"summarized per class only (GIF and animated-IC cases are always repaired)."
msgstr ""

